From: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
Subject: [PATCH 7/8] hw/display/apple-gfx-linux: meson + Kconfig wiring

Add `CONFIG_APPLE_GFX_PCI_LINUX` to `hw/display/Kconfig` with
`default y if PCI_DEVICES`, depending on PCI. Add the meson
gate in `hw/display/meson.build` under a new
`apple_gfx_pci_linux` module set. The meson rule declares the
`libapplegfx-vulkan` dependency with `required: false`, so if
the library is not installed on the build host the device
silently drops out of the build even when the Kconfig symbol
is set - matching how other optional-dep devices (virgl,
rutabaga) gate themselves.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
---
 hw/display/Kconfig      | 10 ++++++++++
 hw/display/meson.build  | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 26 insertions(+)

--- a/hw/display/Kconfig
+++ b/hw/display/Kconfig
@@ -150,3 +150,13 @@ config MAC_PVG_PCI
     bool
     depends on MAC_PVG && PCI
     default y if PCI_DEVICES
+
+config APPLE_GFX_PCI_LINUX
+    bool "Apple ParavirtualizedGraphics PCI device (Linux)"
+    default y if PCI_DEVICES
+    depends on PCI
+    help
+      Enable the Linux-compatible Apple ParavirtualizedGraphics PCI
+      device. Requires libapplegfx-vulkan library with lavapipe Vulkan
+      backend. The runtime dependency is gated at the meson level - if
+      libapplegfx-vulkan is not found via pkg-config, the device
+      source files are dropped from the build even if this symbol is y.
--- a/hw/display/meson.build
+++ b/hw/display/meson.build
@@ -64,6 +64,22 @@ system_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_ATI_VGA', if_true: [files('ati.c', 'ati_2d.c', 'ati_
 system_ss.add(when: [pvg, 'CONFIG_MAC_PVG_PCI'],     if_true: [files('apple-gfx.m', 'apple-gfx-pci.m')])
 system_ss.add(when: [pvg, 'CONFIG_MAC_PVG_MMIO'],    if_true: [files('apple-gfx.m', 'apple-gfx-mmio.m')])

+# Apple ParavirtualizedGraphics PCI device (Linux C port).
+# The runtime dependency is gated at the meson level: if libapplegfx-vulkan
+# is not present on the build host, the device silently drops out of the
+# build (required: false). The Kconfig default-yes-on-PCI_DEVICES is
+# harmless in that case - the meson gate keeps the source files out.
+if config_all_devices.has_key('CONFIG_APPLE_GFX_PCI_LINUX')
+  libapplegfx_vulkan = dependency('libapplegfx-vulkan', required: false)
+  if libapplegfx_vulkan.found()
+    applegfx_ss = ss.source_set()
+    applegfx_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_APPLE_GFX_PCI_LINUX', if_true: [
+      files('apple-gfx-pci-linux.c', 'apple-gfx-common-linux.c'),
+      libapplegfx_vulkan,
+    ])
+    hw_display_modules += {'apple_gfx_pci_linux': applegfx_ss}
+  endif
+endif
+
 if config_all_devices.has_key('CONFIG_VIRTIO_GPU')
   virtio_gpu_ss = ss.source_set()
   virtio_gpu_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_VIRTIO_GPU',
